title: Grateful Dead Live at Deer Creek Music Center on 1990-07-19
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, They Love Each Other, Desolation Row, Row Jimmy, Picasso Moon, Althea > The Promised Land

Set 2

Victim Or The Crime > Foolish Heart > Playing In The Band > China Doll > Uncle John's Band > Drums > Space > All Along The Watchtower > Black Peter > Not Fade Away, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text: Dave strikes again Dave, you are truly gifted with post production skills. Your balanced mixes are a breath of fresh air. I'm getting so tired of rolling off tons of high end to compensate for the hearing loss of certain engineers. This show was so good even Picasso Moon was rocking(and that is saying a lot).

tight show only the dead make shows like this.  you look at the set list and think meh, whatever.  then when you listen to it, the heavens open.

highlights are the jack straw opener and the playin' jam.  but overall, super high quality playing, which is saying something on this tour and even compared against the night before's show--which is another 5-star show.
